The paper presents a framework for inductive representation learning on large graphs, which is a topic that falls under the sub-field of machine learning on graphs. The paper specifically focuses on node classification tasks and leverages node feature information to generate embeddings for previously unseen data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques for text attributes, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
